Recommends: xdotool | wtype
Suggests: ollama
Description: Open-source voice-to-text that acts as a seamless whisper keyboard
 OpenHush is a privacy-first voice-to-text tool that runs entirely on your
 local machine. No cloud, no subscriptions, no telemetry. Just fast, accurate
 transcription using OpenAI's Whisper model.
 .
 Features:
  - Push-to-talk and toggle recording modes
  - Auto-paste transcribed text at cursor
  - GPU acceleration (NVIDIA CUDA, AMD ROCm, Vulkan)
  - 99+ language support with auto-detection
  - Voice Activity Detection for continuous dictation
  - Custom vocabulary for domain-specific terms
  - LLM-powered grammar correction via Ollama
